/caption="You have completed all tasks! Many thanks for your participation! 
The purpose of the study is to investigate how people estimate time when given immediate feedback on actual time usage.
In research on estimation of time, it is often difficult for researchers to know what is the most 'correct' estimate, because tasks are often completed only once.
By giving brief tasks (the reaction time task) we are able to investigate how the estimates relate to a larger distribution of actual outcomes. This will help us find better estimation methods that may be useful in the estimation of larger tasks and projects.
If you have any questions please contact Torleif Halkjelsvik, Adjunct Research Scientist at Simula Metropolitan Centre for Digital Engineering, e-mail: torleif@simula.no"
</surveypage>

