<page intro1>
Find the right letter!
^^We will show you some letters on the screen. Your task is to press the letter we present to you (it does not matter whether you type capital or lowercase letters). If you hit the wrong key, you need to try another until you press the right one. Focus on the line "____" in the middle of the screen before each new trial.
</page>

<page intro1ErrorCond>
Find the right letter!
^^We will show you some letters on the screen. Your task is to press the letter we present to you (it does not matter whether you type capital or lowercase letters). If you hit the wrong key, you need to try another until you press the right one. You can only do two mistakes in each set. Focus on the line "____" in the middle of the screen before each new trial.
</page>



<page etterkunlexical>
In addition to the letter task, we also want you to estimate your reaction time.
Please provide the time (in number of milliseconds) you believe you will use to hit the correct key. A millisecond may be an unfamiliar unit for you, but do your best (make a guess) and after a while you will get used to measurements in milliseconds.^^
Your reaction time in the letter task is measured from the time the letter appears until you hit the correct letter.
</page>

<page etterkunlexicalErrorCond>
You hit the wrong key <% values.errorcount %> times. In addition to the letter task, we also want you to estimate your reaction time.
Please provide the time (in number of milliseconds) you believe you will use to hit the correct key. A millisecond may be an unfamiliar unit for you, but do your best (make a guess) and after a while you will get used to measurements in milliseconds.^^
Your reaction time in the letter task is measured from the time the letter appears until you hit the correct letter, but only if your first response is the correct letter. If you hit one of the other keys first, the trial does not count and you will not get feedback on your reaction time.
</page>



<page write2slide>
Instead of writing your estimate, we now want you to provide your estimate on a number line. Press spacebar to start.
</page>

<page write2slideErrorCond>
You hit the wrong key <% values.errorcount %> times. It is important that you make as few mistakes as possible (maximum 2 mistakes per set). Instead of writing your estimate, we now want you to provide your estimate on a number line. Press spacebar to start.
</page>


**********************Orginal condition
<page ettertestblokk1>
To get good data on judgments and performance we would like you to complete four sets. 
You have completed the first and can now start the second. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can in the letter-pressing task.
</page>

<page ettertestblokk2>
You have completed two sets and can now start the third out of four. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can in the letter-pressing task.
</page>

<page ettertestblokk3>
You have completed three sets and can start the last set (a somewat longer set) after a few questions.
</page>


<page lastset>
Now, back to the reaction time and estimation task. This is the last set. It is longer than the previous sets. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can without making mistakes in the letter-pressing task.
</page>

**ERROR CONDITION:
<page ettertestblokk1ErrorCond>
In this set you made <% values.errorcount %> mistake(s). 
It is important that you make as few mistakes as possible (maximum 2 mistakes per set). 
To get good data on judgments and performance we would like you to complete four sets. 
You have completed the first and can now start the second. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can without making mistakes in the letter-pressing task.
</page>

<page ettertestblokk2ErrorCond>
In this set you made <% values.errorcount %> mistake(s). 
It is important that you make as few mistakes as possible (maximum 2 mistakes per set). 
You have completed two sets and can now start the third out of four. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can without making mistakes in the letter-pressing task.
</page>

<page ettertestblokk3ErrorCond>
In this set you made <% values.errorcount %> mistake(s). 
It is important that you make as few mistakes as possible (maximum 2 mistakes per set). 
You have completed three sets and can start the last set (a somewhat longer set) after a few questions. 
</page>

<page lastsetErrorCond>
Now, back to the reaction time and estimation task. It is important that you make as few mistakes as possible (maximum 2 mistakes per set). 
This is the last set. It is longer than the previous sets. ^^Please take your time and estimate as accurately as you can, and then perform as quickly as you can without making mistakes in the letter-pressing task.
</page>


<page end>
You have completed all tasks! Many thanks for your participation! ^
The purpose with the study is to investigate how people estimate time when given immediate feedback on actual time usage.
In research on estimation of time it is often difficult for researchers to know what is the most "correct" estimate, because tasks are often completed only once.
By giving brief reaction time tasks we are able to investigate how the estimates relate to a larger distribution of actual outcomes. This will help us find better estimation methods that can be relevant for the estimation of larger tasks and projects.
^If you have any questions please contact Torleif Halkjelsvik, Adjunct Research Scientist at Simula Metropolitan Centre for Digital Engineering, e-mail: torleif@simula.no
</page>
