<text scalemax>
/items = ("shape.line.height: <%shape.line.height%>")
/ position = (0%, 0%)
/ color = red
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 1.50%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</text>

<text proportionscorevalue>
/items = ("expressions.proportionscorevalue: <%expressions.proportionscorevalue%>")
/ position = (0%, 0%)
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 1.50%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ color = red
</text>


<text valuepredictiontxtverdi>
/ items = ("<%values.valueprediction%>")
/ position = (50%, 20%)
/ color = white
/ size = (0.001%, 0.001%)
</text>

<text valueoutcometxtverdi>
/ items = ("<%values.valueoutcome%>")
/ position = (50%, 30%)
/ color = white
/ size = (0.001%, 0.001%)
</text>






**Set max of scale to four times incremental SD above incremental mean response latency?? the 100 is just to simplify the rounding
/ ontrialbegin = [values.scalemax=round((values.MMA+4*sqrt(values.IncVar))/100)*100]

**Set max of scale to twice the mean instead?
<trial setmax>
/ ontrialbegin = [values.scalemax=round(2*values.MMA/100)*100]
/ stimulusframes = [1=setmax]
/ response = timeout(0)
</trial>

<text setmax>
/ items = ("scalemax:<%values.scalemax%>; movingav:<%values.MMA%>; IncVar:<%values.IncVar%>, IncSD:<%sqrt(values.IncVar)%>")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial Narrow", 2.38%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ position = (100%, 100%)
</text>

/ ontrialbegin = [expressions.scalemax=values.MMA+3*(sqrt(values.IncVar))


